# NYT Design System Cursor Rules

## Typography Rules
- Always use NYT proprietary fonts from the fonts/ directory
- Headlines: Use Cheltenham (fonts/cheltenham/) or Karnak (fonts/karnak/) families
- Body text: Use Franklin (fonts/franklin/) or Imperial (fonts/imperial/) families
- Reference web-fonts.css for proper @font-face declarations
- Apply typography tokens from misc tokens/tpl-typography.css for consistent sizing

## Color and Theming
- Use color tokens from misc tokens/ directory - never hardcode hex values
- Light theme: Reference tpl-color-tokens-light.css
- Dark theme: Reference tpl-color-tokens-dark.css
- Semantic colors: Use ink_semantic-colors-default-(light).css or ink_semantic-colors-inverse-(dark).css
- Maintain WCAG AA contrast ratios for accessibility

## Layout and Spacing
- Use NYT Tachyons classes from nyt-tachyons/ for all layout and spacing
- Reference size tokens from misc tokens/tpl-size-tokens.css for consistent measurements
- Implement mobile-first responsive design approach
- Use semantic HTML5 elements for proper document structure

## Brand Guidelines
- Include NYT logo from logos/New_York_Times_T_icon.svg when appropriate
- Follow brand guidelines from misc context/brand-book.html
- Adhere to UX principles outlined in misc context/ux-tenents.md
- Maintain brand consistency in all visual elements

## Component Standards
- Create reusable, composable components
- Include proper ARIA labels and accessibility attributes
- Implement focus states and keyboard navigation
- Use consistent naming conventions (BEM or similar)
- Include hover and active states for interactive elements

## Code Quality
- Write clean, semantic HTML
- Use CSS custom properties for theme-able values
- Include proper TypeScript types for React components
- Add JSDoc comments for component props and functions
- Ensure components work across modern browsers

## Performance
- Optimize font loading with font-display: swap
- Use appropriate image formats and sizes
- Implement lazy loading for non-critical content
- Minimize CSS and JavaScript bundle sizes
- Follow Core Web Vitals best practices

When generating code, always reference specific files from this repository and explain which design tokens or assets are being used.
